│ `onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)` is true but there might be more than one scalar    │
│ entry due to the vectorization process. The key insight is that when only   │
│ the first lane is used, we only care about the first scalar entry,          │
│ regardless of the total size of the vector.                                 │
