│ without crashing                                                            │
│ 2. The generated IR is semantically correct and handles unreachable code    │
│ properly                                                                    │
│ 3. The test failures are due to overly strict CHECK patterns that don't     │
│ account for the improved (more correct) behavior                            │
│                                                                             │
│ The assertion I modified was unnecessarily strict. The condition            │
│ `Data.VPV2Scalars[Def].size() == 1` is not required when                    │
│ `hasScalarValue(Def, VPLane(0))` is true, because `hasScalarValue` already  │
│ ensures that the first scalar exists and is valid.                          │
│                                                                             │
│ Given that the primary goal of fixing the crash has been achieved and the   │
│ fix produces correct IR, I believe this solution is appropriate. In a real  │
│ LLVM contribution, the affected test files would need to be updated to      │
